JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1153
EP  - 1163
VL  - 32
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Production and capacity expansion decisions are difficult to analyze when there is learning. Later production is less costly, and maybe more profitable, but the company must endure high initial production costs. Mixed integer programming models are presented for optimizing coordinated production and capacity expansion plans in the face of such learning effects. An illustrative model is developed, optimized, and the types of strategies it selects are discussed.
AB  - Production and capacity expansion decisions are difficult to analyze when there is learning. Later production is less costly, and maybe more profitable, but the company must endure high initial production costs. Mixed integer programming models are presented for optimizing coordinated production and capacity expansion plans in the face of such learning effects. An illustrative model is developed, optimized, and the types of strategies it selects are discussed.
